The paper deals with evaluating the accuracy of object detectors and trackers, which is a common problem in computer vision. The paper specifically addresses the issue of evaluating detectors and trackers on densely segmented datasets, which suggests a focus on computer vision and image analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a new accuracy measure, which involves normalization and optimization, suggesting a focus on machine learning and optimization, which are covered in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with object tracking, which is a subfield of robotics, suggesting a possible fit with cs.RO (Robotics and Control). Finally, the paper involves the use of evaluation frameworks, which suggests a possible fit with cs.MM (Multimedia).
